name: maize grain to generic market for energy feed | energy feed, gross | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/1201/documentation

This activity is a linking activity, i.e. it connects maize grain with generic protein feed market. Maize grain is used partially as a feed for animals, thus traded on generic feed market with other protein - containing products.

This linking activity has the maize grain as an input (negative reference product) and protein and energy feed as outputs.
category: C:Manufacturing/10:Manufacture of food products/108:Manufacture of prepared animal feeds/1080:Manufacture of prepared animal feeds

exchanges.description:
Calculated based on literature value from Agroscope database (http://www.feed-alp.admin.ch). Agroscope (http://www.agroscope.admin.ch/org/index.html?lang=en) is a research institute which belongs to the Swiss Federal Office for Agriculture. The gross energy in maize grain might vary depending on the amount of fat present in the grain. This grain is considered to have app. 6.3% of fat. 

It is estimated, that 90% of the maize grain goes to the generic market for protein feed.
